section.def:
Commission
                (廉政公署) means the Independent Commission Against
            Corruption established under section 3;

officer
                (廉署人員) means an officer of the Commission
            appointed under section 8;

paragraph.content:
the offence of obtaining pecuniary advantage by deception under
                        section 18 of the Theft Ordinance (Cap.
                        210);

detained there if an officer of the rank of Senior Commission Against
                    Corruption Officer or above considers it necessary for the purpose of further
                    inquiries;

subparagraph.content:
on his depositing such reasonable sum of money as an officer of the
                        rank of Senior Commission Against Corruption Officer or above may require;
                        or
